 <br />
     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> I have another Sauron deck, but in it I focus on the stronger, expensive minions. In this deck I decided to stray away from those and use the slightly weaker, cheaper minions. The following is a basic plan of how this deck will ideally play.<br />
<br />
Bid high for burdens, as your site 1 allows you to have get another hobbit by the name of Pippin. Hopefully you&#39;ll have a frying pan or two to power up your hobbits, if not use your site 2 game text/Boromir and exert a hobbit and Boromir to make that hobbit strength +5 total. Try to double move to site 3 while using this method.<br />
<br />
After that I would advise against double moving to site 5 because of the massive pool it would create. So, after stopping at site 4, your opponent might be able to get ahead of you with a double move, so use your added pool to get out a swarm of cheap minions (hopefully overwhelming Frodo early, if not there are enough minions to get him in the end).<br />
<br />
After site 5, if a balrog comes out, try to send Merry and Pippin at him, hopefully using Boromir to stop them from being overwhelmed (that doesn&#39;t always work, but if not they&#39;re expendable). Double move if possible.<br />
<br />
Heal the wounds at site 6 allowing your exert abilities to start all over again (Frying pans annihilate Moria Swarms). A few well-placed double moves from there and your at site 9 very quickly. <br />
<br />
If delays force your opponent to reach your site 9, Amon Hen allows you to draw a card for each burden, allowing you to draw more minions (there are 20 Minions in the deck). And with its shadow number of 8, it will allow you to play at the very least 4 minions, more likely 5 or 6, easily overwhelming most fellowships and allowing you to assign multiple guys to Frodo. If I had better cards, I would add another minion and a gift of boats to allow you to reach site 9 faster.<br />
<br />
I just built this deck this morning, and only tested it once against my brother, but it won. Try it, it might win for you! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php?PHPSESSID=8c6a6613a872554aaf15d0c335efde91">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=24979&PHPSESSID=8c6a6613a872554aaf15d0c335efde91"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=24979&PHPSESSID=8c6a6613a872554aaf15d0c335efde91" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=8c6a6613a872554aaf15d0c335efde91">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
